{"content": "<p>Many giga brain blockchain artists offer more to delve in to than the face value of art. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">My <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TwoBitBears?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@TwoBitBears</a> Itzel &amp; Karkai had a new baby on their bearsgiving camping trip! Please welcome bright-eyed lil&#39; Kilo Farmer... Uncle Fvck &amp; Deafbeef Aoki also came to join in the celebration<br /><br />flowers can be sent to <a href=\"https://t.co/tF6Ooj7xDH\">https://t.co/tF6Ooj7xDH</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/onchain?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#onchain</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/bearsgiving?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#bearsgiving</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/wow?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#wow</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/EFImGEilZZ\">pic.twitter.com/EFImGEilZZ</a></p>&mdash; bliargh (@Bliargh) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Bliargh/status/1464708974733893632?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">November 27, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></figure><p>Introducing 'Beanie Aversano the Happy Brown Bear #4449.' Yes, every bear is named after people that have reputations of their own in NFTs. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/455d5d086ab04402349ed715403c8ab0.svg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0x8ed25b735a788f4f7129db736fc64f3a241137b8/4448\">Beanie Aversano the Happy Brown Bear #4449</a> from Two Bit Bears</figcaption></figure><p>Where you might see an overly simplistic two pixel image, the creators of the Two Bit Bears invite you to explore further. There are four species of bear. Brown, black, polar and the super rare panda bear. Beanie Aversano bear belongs to the most common brown bear species.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.25.53-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"838\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.25.53-PM.png 600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.25.53-PM.png 838w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Now that we know the species of bears in the Two Bit Bear collection, let's review the artistic merit of the bears in two parts. </p><p>Firstly, the body fur and then the head fur. Both have 500 is different permutations. The <a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbears?search[sortAscending]=true&amp;search[sortBy]=PRICE&amp;search[stringTraits][0][name]=Realistic%20Body%20Fur&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][0]=rgb%2898%2C64%2C32%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][1]=rgb%289%2C9%2C9%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][2]=rgb%289%2C9%2C10%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][3]=rgb%288%2C8%2C9%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][4]=rgb%288%2C8%2C8%29\">rarest body fur combinations</a> of red, green and blue (RGB) strike the darkest pose.  </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-wide\"><a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbears?search[sortAscending]=true&amp;search[sortBy]=PRICE&amp;search[stringTraits][0][name]=Realistic%20Body%20Fur&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][0]=rgb%2898%2C64%2C32%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][1]=rgb%289%2C9%2C9%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][2]=rgb%289%2C9%2C10%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][3]=rgb%288%2C8%2C9%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][4]=rgb%288%2C8%2C8%29\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.29.10-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"717\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.29.10-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.29.10-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.29.10-PM.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w2400/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.29.10-PM.png 2400w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px\"></a></figure><p>The <a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbears?search[sortAscending]=true&amp;search[sortBy]=PRICE&amp;search[stringTraits][0][name]=Realistic%20Head%20Fur&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][0]=rgb%2886%2C89%2C107%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][1]=rgb%2885%2C90%2C105%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][2]=rgb%2873%2C77%2C90%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][3]=rgb%2873%2C76%2C88%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][4]=rgb%2870%2C71%2C84%29\">rarest head fur combinations</a> are also at the darker end of the spectrum, and are dominated by the black bear species.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-wide\"><a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbears?search[sortAscending]=true&amp;search[sortBy]=PRICE&amp;search[stringTraits][0][name]=Realistic%20Head%20Fur&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][0]=rgb%2886%2C89%2C107%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][1]=rgb%2885%2C90%2C105%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][2]=rgb%2873%2C77%2C90%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][3]=rgb%2873%2C76%2C88%29&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][4]=rgb%2870%2C71%2C84%29\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.31.39-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"710\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.31.39-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.31.39-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.31.39-PM.png 1600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w2400/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.31.39-PM.png 2400w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px\"></a></figure><p>Is MintFace being serious here? Yes. <em>We like the bears.</em> Getting the technicals right can add a whole lot more value to an art collection minted as an NFT. Two Bit Bears offer the owner limitless SVG scalability, with SVG meaning scalable vector graphics. That's good news if you desire your art displayed large. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-wide\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/1-UGz6Hfray8Ev0r6--dHPow.jpeg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1400\" height=\"418\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/1-UGz6Hfray8Ev0r6--dHPow.jpeg 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/1-UGz6Hfray8Ev0r6--dHPow.jpeg 1000w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/1-UGz6Hfray8Ev0r6--dHPow.jpeg 1400w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px\"></figure><p>There's more to the bears. So keep reading.</p><h3 id=\"the-cubs\">The Cubs</h3><p>In real life, bears have cubs. In the immutable word of the blockchain, Two Bit Bears can also grow up to become bears. All you need to be able to breed is:</p><ul><li>two bears (of course)</li><li>a honey processor</li></ul><p>Ok, yeah so you need a honey processor. What's a honey processor? ...I hear you ask. It was a free token shared to bear owners on 2nd November. There's 1,300 Honey Processors and 654 owners at last count. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0x65b7990ab726ef573c176bb8b9b5464de6ea6c89/0\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.36.42-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1836\" height=\"938\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/\nScreen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.36.42-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.36.42-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.36.42-PM.png 1600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.36.42-PM.png 1836w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></a><figcaption><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0x65b7990ab726ef573c176bb8b9b5464de6ea6c89/0\">Honey Processor</a> for Two Bit Bears</figcaption></figure><p>So go and get a <a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0x65b7990ab726ef573c176bb8b9b5464de6ea6c89/0\">Honey Processor</a> and two bears if you plan on breeding at a price of around 0.15 eth plus gas. </p><p>The breeding happens in a <a href=\"https://cubs.cloud\">special breeding enclosure</a>. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.11.53-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1738\" height=\"912\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.11.53-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.11.53-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.11.53-PM.png 1600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.11.53-PM.png 1738w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://cubs.cloud/breed.html\">Two Bit Bears Breeding Enclosure</a></figcaption></figure><p>I bred 'Hunter Vee the Happy Black Bear #4460' with 'Squarci Aversano the Happy Black Bear #4461' who judging by the numbers must have lived in the bear cave next door.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.17.08-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1738\" height=\"932\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.17.08-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.17.08-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.17.08-PM.png 1600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.17.08-PM.png 1738w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>As you know from IRL, breeding can be expensive. There's no difference here. Gas costs for each parent bear, plus the honey, plus of course the breeding. Here's how Hunter Vee and Squarci Aversano met. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><iframe width=\"200\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/RXXUseZLJzE?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe></figure><p>You'll get to see how your bears met each other two if you breed.</p><p>...and you'll get to meet your cub or cubs! The two bears bred one of a three potential cubs. Everybody meet 0xInuarashi Hobbs the Cheerful Black Cub #672!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.24.37-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"980\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.24.37-PM.png 600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-1.24.37-PM.png 900w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://opensea.io/assets/0x488c057cf3dee9ee2e386112e08f2c6d8e58cdfb/672\">0xInuarashi Hobbs the Cheerful Black Cub #672</a></figcaption></figure><p>Otherwise, just get a bear and enjoy the stunning aesthetic quality of it at limitless scalable size. </p><p>Or HODL your honey.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">As we close in on our Two Bit Bears Gen 3 announcement...people still hesitate to breed their Gen 1 Bears because they don&#39;t want to burn their Honey in the process...<br /><br />Yet another observation from a choose your own bear-venture project...<a href=\"https://t.co/cbHXJT5clR\">https://t.co/cbHXJT5clR</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/hSsMezawkg\">pic.twitter.com/hSsMezawkg</a></p>&mdash; Two Bit Bears (@TwoBitBears) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TwoBitBears/status/1464324974018240521?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">November 26, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></figure><p>You're starting to see that the people behind the Two Bit Bears aren't amateurs when it comes to game theory, scarcity and perhaps even bear utility. </p><blockquote>'Clearly we're not a bunch of people that don't know how to use computers.'</blockquote><p>The bear cave gets deeper though. Let's continue.</p><p>Breeding a pair of bears gets you somewhere between one and three cubs. Genetically speaking they will inherent a blend of the moods and fur styles of their parents. Look at the cuteness of the <a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbearsgentwo?search[sortAscending]=true&amp;search[sortBy]=PRICE&amp;search[stringTraits][0][name]=Species&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][0]=Polar\">Polar Cubs</a>!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-wide kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.41.48-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"742\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.41.48-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.41.48-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.41.48-PM.png 1600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.41.48-PM.png 2118w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbearsgentwo?search[sortAscending]=true&amp;search[sortBy]=PRICE&amp;search[stringTraits][0][name]=Species&amp;search[stringTraits][0][values][0]=Polar\">Polar Cubs</a> created from breeding Polar Bears</figcaption></figure><p>Now let's say you missed out on the getting the honey processor needed to breed. There's another way. Adoption. Yep. Adopt a cub and if you decide, you can feed them up and in a crypto week (which is 9 years IRL) you cub will become a fully grown bear. Here's how:</p><ol><li><a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/twobitbearsgentwo?tab=activity\">Adopt a cub on OpenSea</a></li><li>Trigger the growth mechanism (to be released)</li></ol><p>It's completely optional too so if you prefer your cubs cute and cube-like cuddly, then you can keep them young forever. </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-wide kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.51.29-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1706\" height=\"1622\" srcset=\"https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.51.29-PM.png 600w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1000/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.51.29-PM.png 1000w, https://pub-40df8e6473b14a10a093ecf8c80c2f92.r2.dev/size/w1600/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.51.29-PM.png 1600w, https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-28-at-12.51.29-PM.png 1706w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px\"><figcaption><a href=\"https://www.twobitbears.com/quickstartguide\">The evolution of the Two Bit Bears&nbsp;</a></figcaption></figure><p><a href=\"https://\ndiscord.gg/SZ4EvAvS\">Checking in on the Discord</a> can help you get your head around who you'll be joining when you acquire a Two Bit Bear. In real life, polar bears and grizzly bears kept to themselves for almost all of time...until there wasn't enough food to go around and polar bears ventured south. The polar bears met grizzly bears and created...<a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com.au/pizzly-bears-polar-grizzly-hybrid-spread-due-to-climate-crisis-2021-4?r=US&amp;IR=T\">Pizzly bears</a>. The Two Bit Bears let's you decide what kind of cubs you'll create from the bears you get however, they must be the same species (Polar + Polar or Black Bear + Black Bear).</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">GM — Developers, Generative Artists, Collectors &amp; Early Adopters...</p>&mdash; Two Bit Bears (@TwoBitBears) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TwoBitBears/status/1463167645612716064?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">November 23, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></figure><p>This is true performance art on the blockchain. Before you get bearish, you have to decide whether this is a performance you'd like to see. </p><blockquote>\"We are incredibly proud and protective over our Proprietary Bear Rendering Algorithm™ . Without it Two Bit Bears and all future projects on our roadmap would never exist.\" </blockquote><p>Once you're in, it makes sense to stay until the end of the show. They artists want you to celebrate and marvel at the astonishing detail in each Two Bit Bear.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/content/images/2021/11/1-lk4JftAuFFxa9n_28dkN-Q.gif\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\"></figure><p></p><hr /><p><strong><a href=\"https://digital-artist-economy.ghost.io/#/portal/signup\">Subscribe to MintFace</a> and receive new artist features by email.</strong></p><p>If this article has made you curious about getting started with digital art, we also run the <a href=\"https://maven.com/cache/nft-digital-artist-economy\">Digital Artist Economy workshop</a> helping artists create their first digital art through a <a href=\"https://maven.com/cache/nft-digital-artist-economy\">three week programme.</a> Share it with an artist you'd like to see on an NFT marketplace.</p><p><strong>MintFace surfaces great artists and artworks so you don't have to. </strong></p><p><em>Enjoying MintFace? Subscribe for $9 per month.</em></p><p></p>"}